result.notes:
Survey run by Ambios Environmental Consultants Ltd. for Kerr-McGee Oil (UK) plc. All these records relate to "Rostron, Little (1995)  - Lyme Bay Environmental Study Volume 6. Intertidal benthic ecology: Rocky shores" Copy of the report is held at Dorset Environmental Records Centre.

This report forms part of the 'Lyme Bay Environmental Study' series. This volume aimed to provide an assessment of the ecology of a range of rocky shore types in Lyme Bay. Field survey, using MNCR methodology, took place during spring tide periods of May (23rd-28th) and June (22nd - 27th) 1994. 12 sites in Dorset were surveyed (18 sites surveyed overall, 6 were in Devon) - only the Dorset sites have been entered onto the Dorset database. Numerous site photographs appear throughout report.
